    <text id="B2019T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson reports Miss Rowell's arrival as the new teacher, and immediately
                    requests that she be sent a female companion, for Jackson fears the impropriety
                    of her being unaccompanied, and has also struggled to find housing for her.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr> R. M.
                        Manly<lb/>Richmond</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-18"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 18 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Miss Rowell arrived safely at Staunton but I have had great difficulty in finding
                    a boarding place and at last had to rent part of a house occupied by a colored
                    man &amp; wife. I am somewhat embarrassed in this matter and this lady
                    question was the reason I asked so earnestly for a gentleman. Do send Miss <abbr
                        expan="Rowell">R.</abbr> an assistant and companion as soon as possible, you
                    will relieve me immediately for although far from young, I am not old enough to
                    have a solitary and <pb n="2"/>amiable young lady under my charge without fear
                    of being misunderstood by the <unclear>little world</unclear> of disloyalty and
                    censoriousness.</p>

                <p>Excuse my hurried letter but I have been working day or night to 9 or 10 at night
                    on Registration &amp; election and would not have written at all had I not
                    felt compelled to notice the <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <unclear>letter</unclear>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Faithfully</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Thos P. Jackson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
